channel.title: Real Runescape PS, Good Idea?
channel.description:
[center]Hey, I was wondering if you think if i made a RSPS, the exact same as real runescape, Eg- start in Lumbridge, Shops in original places, exp. rate=4 (or something quite low), Teleporting just like runescapes, needing runes to teleport.. 100% on all skills..
Try my best to get it working exactly like rs?
Do you think this is a good idea? :)
Many Thanks, Lee.[/center]

item.title: Real Runescape PS, Good Idea?
item.dc:creator: @Ljelvin1995 Ljelvin1995
item.description:
@Ljelvin1995 wrote:

[quote=“Ix Soulcist xI, post:8, topic:406083”][quote author=Ljelvin1995 link=topic=503081.msg3680472#msg3680472 date=1311494074]

There are quite a lot of developments that goals and what not are the exact same as this, but the fact is that it’s not possible to make a RSPS exactly like RuneScape because RuneScape is so advanced in some kinds of ways, but people do have the potential, but it would take a while.

I know it would take time mate, but i’ve got time now
But i would probably do:
100% Lumbridge.
100% Varrock.
100% Falador
100% Camelot
100% ardy

Then stuff like:
Duel Arena
Castle Wars
Pest Control
Barrows
Basically, the main things

Then put it online, then work on everywhere else afterward?

Lee.
[/quote]
I don’t quite all remember what the pure 317 revision had, and I don’t believe it had all those minigames. Nonetheless, this includes working on the doors as well, don’t forget.[/quote]

I know it does mate Thanks anyways.

Lee
